00:00:52,920 --> 00:00:56,121
  narrator: truck drivers spend 
   a lot of time on the road,   

10
00:00:56,123 --> 00:00:59,524
  so their sleeper rigs become  
     a home away from home.     

11
00:00:59,526 --> 00:01:02,795
  equipped with a refrigerator, 
       tv, and microwave,       

12
00:01:02,797 --> 00:01:04,596
          a sleeper rig         
      is more than a place      

13
00:01:04,598 --> 00:01:06,399
   to bunk down for the night.  

14
00:01:06,401 --> 00:01:08,734
   it can also be a trucker's   
          living space          

15
00:01:08,736 --> 00:01:11,370
  when it's time to pull over.  

16
00:01:12,874 --> 00:01:15,474
     due to the convenience     
        of sleeper rigs,        

17
00:01:15,476 --> 00:01:17,743
       truckers don't need      
      to pull into a hotel      

18
00:01:17,745 --> 00:01:19,278
once they've put in their hours.

19
00:01:19,280 --> 00:01:21,413
 instead, they simply pull over 

20
00:01:21,415 --> 00:01:24,683
 since they're hauling their own
    sleeping accommodations.    

21
00:01:24,685 --> 00:01:29,154
 this factory builds custom rigs
 based on drivers' preferences. 

22
00:01:29,156 --> 00:01:32,291
 production starts by installing
      the steel frame rails     

23
00:01:32,293 --> 00:01:34,493
    for the vehicle's frame,    
           or chassis.          

24
00:01:34,495 --> 00:01:36,562
        first, machinists       
         place the rails        

25
00:01:36,564 --> 00:01:38,230
   in an upside down position   

26
00:01:38,232 --> 00:01:40,299
         and wire it for        
        indicator lights        

27
00:01:40,301 --> 00:01:42,702
and other electrical components.

28
00:01:42,704 --> 00:01:44,970
         they run hoses         
       for the air brakes       

29
00:01:44,972 --> 00:01:47,974
       and to deliver fuel      
         to the engine.         

30
00:01:47,976 --> 00:01:51,977
  they link the two frame rails 
      with cross members...     

31
00:01:51,979 --> 00:01:56,616
 and bolt an engine support rail
 to the front of the framework. 

32
00:01:57,785 --> 00:02:00,519
    a crane moves the chassis   
         down the line,         

33
00:02:00,521 --> 00:02:03,122
  while a second crane carries  
        three wheel axles       

34
00:02:03,124 --> 00:02:05,057
    over to the first crane.    

35
00:02:05,059 --> 00:02:07,994
   technicians guide the axles  
          into position         

36
00:02:07,996 --> 00:02:11,263
       as they're lowered       
         onto the frame.        

37
00:02:11,265 --> 00:02:15,067
    the team bolts the axles    
         to the chassis.        

38
00:02:15,069 --> 00:02:17,803
     a rollover crane flips     
           the chassis          

39
00:02:17,805 --> 00:02:21,707
   and places it on a pedestal  
that will move it down the line.

40
00:02:23,945 --> 00:02:26,879
   next, the fifth wheel hitch  
          is installed.         

41
00:02:26,881 --> 00:02:30,216
     that's used to connect     
    the truck to the trailer.   

42
00:02:30,218 --> 00:02:33,152
                     ♪♪         

43
00:02:33,154 --> 00:02:36,088
   the team secures the hitch   
       with clamping bolts      

44
00:02:36,090 --> 00:02:38,757
            to ensure           
     it's securely in place.    

45
00:02:38,759 --> 00:02:40,359
                     ♪♪         

46
00:02:40,361 --> 00:02:41,827
   the engine and transmission  

47
00:02:41,829 --> 00:02:44,296
        are now connected       
         to the chassis.        

48
00:02:44,298 --> 00:02:48,100
                     ♪♪         

49
00:02:48,102 --> 00:02:51,369
        the team installs       
      the diesel fuel tank.     

50
00:02:51,371 --> 00:02:53,839
 metal straps are wrapped around
            the tank,           

51
00:02:53,841 --> 00:02:58,444
    and brackets are fastened   
  to the center of the chassis. 

52
00:02:58,446 --> 00:03:00,713
   machinists mount the tires   
           and wheels           

53
00:03:00,715 --> 00:03:03,115
    onto the axles in pairs.    

54
00:03:03,117 --> 00:03:06,852
   this dual wheel system has   
a greater load-carrying capacity

55
00:03:06,854 --> 00:03:09,722
      than a single wheel.      

56
00:03:09,724 --> 00:03:12,658
     using a multi-spindled     
          torque tool,          

57
00:03:12,660 --> 00:03:16,629
      a technician tightens     
        all the lug nuts        

58
00:03:16,631 --> 00:03:21,667
     and writes identifying     
    information on the wheel.   

59
00:03:21,669 --> 00:03:25,070
          now it's over         
    to the industrial robots.   

60
00:03:25,072 --> 00:03:28,207
 these machines assemble the cab
         and the sleeper        

61
00:03:28,209 --> 00:03:31,543
     and rivet the walls of     
    the structures to frames.   

62
00:03:31,545 --> 00:03:34,746
                     ♪♪         

63
00:03:34,748 --> 00:03:36,816
    with speed and precision,   

64
00:03:36,818 --> 00:03:40,018
      the industrial robots     
        install the roof        

65
00:03:40,020 --> 00:03:43,522
        and pipe sealant        
    on top of the cab frame.    

66
00:03:45,293 --> 00:03:48,694
     a crane lowers the roof    
          onto the cab          

67
00:03:48,696 --> 00:03:51,296
     and bolts the structure    
            together.           

68
00:03:51,298 --> 00:03:54,033
           meanwhile,           
     other industrial robots    

69
00:03:54,035 --> 00:03:56,969
     paint the cab, sleeper,    
            and hood.           

70
00:03:56,971 --> 00:03:59,772
      the color is usually      
        a custom choice,        

71
00:03:59,774 --> 00:04:04,176
  as are the size and amenities 
         of the sleeper.        

72
00:04:04,178 --> 00:04:09,114
   a team slides the dashboard  
    subassembly into the cab.   

73
00:04:09,116 --> 00:04:11,584
     they bolt the dashboard    
           to the cab           

74
00:04:11,586 --> 00:04:15,521
   and connect the components   
    to the rest of the truck.   

75
00:04:15,523 --> 00:04:18,156
     this is an inside look     
       at the sleeper cab,      

76
00:04:18,158 --> 00:04:21,327
      which has been wired      
      for lights and heat.      

77
00:04:23,463 --> 00:04:28,267
       technicians install      
         the cabinetry.         

78
00:04:28,269 --> 00:04:31,003
         other features         
     inside the sleeper cab     

79
00:04:31,005 --> 00:04:34,940
    include cabinets equipped   
 with a radio, charger outlets, 

80
00:04:34,942 --> 00:04:37,676
          cup holders,          
       fold-up bunk beds,       

81
00:04:37,678 --> 00:04:40,212
        and mini fridge.        

82
00:04:40,214 --> 00:04:43,148
  once all interior components  
         are installed,         

83
00:04:43,150 --> 00:04:46,485
        the team connects       
     the sleeper to the cab.    

84
00:04:46,487 --> 00:04:49,555
         then they bolt         
    the two pieces together.    

85
00:04:49,557 --> 00:04:52,091
                     ♪♪         

86
00:04:52,093 --> 00:04:54,827
  the cab and sleeper assembly  
          is now ready          

87
00:04:54,829 --> 00:04:56,895
  to be mounted to the chassis. 

88
00:04:56,897 --> 00:04:59,598
  a crane lowers it into place. 

89
00:05:02,236 --> 00:05:05,571
    the team secures the hood   
       to the front rail.       

90
00:05:05,573 --> 00:05:08,307
  the hood contains a mechanism 
       that will allow it       

91
00:05:08,309 --> 00:05:10,509
   to open and close with ease  

92
00:05:10,511 --> 00:05:12,911
  and lock in an open position. 

93
00:05:12,913 --> 00:05:15,047
    next, the assembled truck   

94
00:05:15,049 --> 00:05:17,249
            heads to            
  the wheel alignment station.  

95
00:05:17,251 --> 00:05:20,252
  there, an inspector monitors  
       alignment readouts       

96
00:05:20,254 --> 00:05:22,922
  from lasers and 3-d cameras.  

97
00:05:22,924 --> 00:05:24,456
 this information lets them know

98
00:05:24,458 --> 00:05:27,192
     the wheel's positioning    
          on the axle.          

99
00:05:27,194 --> 00:05:28,861
       based on the data,       

100
00:05:28,863 --> 00:05:32,398
 he loosens the bolts that hold 
     the axles to the wheels    

101
00:05:32,400 --> 00:05:33,932
       and turns the axle       

102
00:05:33,934 --> 00:05:36,468
             to make            
   any additional adjustments.  

103
00:05:36,470 --> 00:05:39,471
                     ♪♪         

104
00:05:39,473 --> 00:05:42,474
     once all the technical     
  modifications have been made, 

105
00:05:42,476 --> 00:05:45,878
   technicians lock a kingpin   
   into the fifth wheel hitch   

106
00:05:45,880 --> 00:05:49,481
 and turn the wheels to confirm 
   that everything is secure.   

107
00:05:49,483 --> 00:05:53,152
 this truck is now ready to hit 
    the road and get to work.   

